Workshop Highlights:
Explore how genetic diversity is distributed across landscapes and influenced by environmental features.
Learn to process environmental data using GIS, analyse genetic variation and identify local adaptation using Sambada.
Gain insights into planning experiments, sampling designs, and interpreting results for evolutionary biology and conservation studies.
